Initialize a new workspace

This command will create the source folder, and place a template configuration
file in it.

Usage:
  bashly init [--minimal]
  bashly init (-h|--help)

Options:
  -m --minimal
    Use a minimal configuration file (without commands)

  -h --help
    Show this help

Environment Variables:
  BASHLY_SOURCE_DIR
    The path to use for creating the configuration file [default: src]
